com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.properties
Interface PropertiesLoader

public interface PropertiesLoader

Loads groups of Java properties, checks for correctness, and carefully logs any overrides.

To construct new instances, see PropertiesLoaderUtils.newInstance().

Author:
Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)

load

Properties load(List<? extends InputSource2> inputSourceList)
                throws PropertiesLoaderException
Loads Java properties sequentially from a list of input sources. Properties from later input sources (higher indices) override earlier input sources (lower indices).

About logging:

  • Each properties source is logged at level INFO.
  • The number of properties found is logged at level DEBUG.
  • Each property (key and value) is logged at level TRACE.
  • Overriding properties are logged at level TRACE.

To load properties to a different collection, see load(List, MapBuilderFactory).

Parameters:
inputSourceList - one or more input sources to load properties
Returns:
new Properties instance
Throws:
NullPointerException - if inputSourceList (or any element) is null
IllegalArgumentException - if number of elements in inputSourceList is zero
PropertiesLoaderException -
  • if input source cannot be read
  • if properties from an input source fail policy (duplicates, etc.)
See Also:
load(List, MapBuilderFactory)
